Tanzanian singer Nandy is set to release an exclusively gospel EP this year. The singe is also ready to make her own record label. Speaking at a press conference on Friday, she said, "Last year, I gifted fans with an album called African Princess. This year, I'm releasing a gospel-only EP." Adding, "I also thinking of a record label and it will only feature gospel artistes" Nandy is known for secular songs. However, she has done a couple of gospel covers. She confessed she was supposed to be signed by Diamond Paltnumz under WCB but went for a competition, in which she emerged among the finalists and was later taken in by Tanzanian House of Talent.